  "response": "Not at all! It is perfectly acceptable for a girl to make the first move in dating and relationships. In fact, many people appreciate the initiative and confidence it shows. Relationships progress best when both parties feel comfortable expressing their feelings and intentions, regardless of traditional gender roles. Ultimately, what matters most is mutual respect, consent, and genuine interest between both individuals. Everyone's approach to dating can be different, and there is no \"wrong\" way to start a relationship as long as it is respectful and consensual.",
